    {
      "id": "3cfd6087_5594b3c4",
      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/ncmp/impl/inventory/NcmpPersistenceImpl.java",
      "patchset_number": 13,
      "line": 108,
      "message": "In dataRestController Object jsondata is updated as String nodedata, Initially the JSON payload was mapped to on Object as jsonobjectMapper.asJsonString(jsondata) to convert to JSON string. By updating JSON payload as a string in requestBody schema the API directly expects as JSON string. Due to this need to dataNodes.toString()",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7840,
        "name": "Rudrangi Anupriya",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "ra00745022@techmahindra.com",
        "username": "anupriya63"
      },
      "updated": "2024-11-20 11:00:17.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "f6ab3ab8_3a7b331e",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "e9ecca7b_997e2f5f",
      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/ncmp/impl/inventory/NcmpPersistenceImpl.java",
      "patchset_number": 14,
      "line": 108,
      "message": "toString is definitely not the ideal thing to do here.\nSince the ContentType is definitely JSON then why not use jsonObjectMapper.asJsonString(dataNodes) method and test your scenario.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7965,
        "name": "Priyank Maheshwari",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "priyank.maheshwari@est.tech",
        "username": "mpriyank"
      },
      "updated": "2024-11-20 15:24:18.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "a071f29d_204c1e4e",
      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/ncmp/impl/inventory/NcmpPersistenceImpl.java",
      "patchset_number": 14,
      "line": 108,
      "message": "dataNodes as collection was used initially when handling only JSON content because JSON objects could be directly mapped to java objects and collections. Here now XML support is introduced, so payload may not be easily map to dataNode object(as XML nodes might not have a direct mapping to Java objects)so dataNodes.toString() converts collection to string which is like a generic payload which is passed to cpsDataService irrespective of the contentType.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7840,
        "name": "Rudrangi Anupriya",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "ra00745022@techmahindra.com",
        "username": "anupriya63"
      },
